# .dockleignore — suppressed Dockle CIS Benchmark findings
#
# Format:  CIS-ID or DKL-ID
#
# Rules:
#   - Document the justification inline as a comment above each suppression.
#   - Review suppressions when base images are upgraded or when the Kubernetes
#     health-check strategy changes.
#
# CIS-DI-0005: Enable Content trust for Docker
#   Suppressed because Docker Content Trust (DCT) is not enforced in this CI
#   environment. Image integrity is instead provided by Cosign signing
#   (sign-images job in build-images.yml) and SLSA provenance attestation
#   (frontend-provenance / temporal-worker-provenance jobs). Revisit if DCT is
#   adopted as an additional layer.
CIS-DI-0005

# CIS-DI-0006: Add HEALTHCHECK instruction to the container image
#   Suppressed because container-level HEALTHCHECK is not required in this project:
#   health probing is delegated to Kubernetes liveness/readiness probes defined
#   in the Helm chart deployment templates (charts/app/templates/frontend-deployment.yaml
#   and charts/app/templates/temporal-worker-deployment.yaml). Adding a HEALTHCHECK
#   to the Dockerfile would duplicate that logic without benefit in the Kubernetes
#   runtime environment. Revisit if the images are deployed outside of Kubernetes
#   (e.g. docker-compose for local dev with health checks).
CIS-DI-0006

# CIS-DI-0010: Do not store credential in environment variables/files
#   Suppressed because this is a false positive from the official nginx:alpine base
#   image. Dockle flags the variable KEY_SHA512 that appears in the nginx base
#   image's RUN layer. KEY_SHA512 holds a SHA-512 hash of the nginx package
#   signing key used to verify the integrity of the downloaded signing key
#   (https://nginx.org/keys/nginx_signing.rsa.pub). It is a cryptographic
#   verification hash, not a credential or secret. The nginx Docker image is an
#   official Docker Hub image maintained by the nginx team; this pattern is
#   intentional and well-understood. Revisit if nginx changes its key-pinning
#   approach in a future base image release.
CIS-DI-0010
# DKL-DI-0006: Avoid latest tag
#   Suppressed for local builds and scan-only tags (scan-<sha> and latest).
#   Production deploys use immutable SHA-tagged images set by the CI pipeline.
#   The mutable 'latest' tag is used only for local development convenience.
DKL-DI-0006
